The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Six injured in mishaps
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Six injured in mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A 60-year-old man was seriously injured after being hit from behind by a speeding vehicle near Nicco Park on Sunday evening.        
	Sukumar Maity, a member of a wedding band, lay bleeding on the road for about 45 minutes before pedestrians and police took him to Bidhannagar sub-divisional hospital. He was transferred to NRS Hospital.        
	In another mishap, five persons were injured after being thrown off a rickshaw when it was hit by a car near City Centre in Salt Lake. The five were taken to Bidhannagar sub-divisional hospital.                                                                                                                                                                          
